# Pagination & Filtering Rules

## Pagination

All list endpoints must support pagination:
- Query parameters: `page` (default: 1), `pageSize` (default: 20, max: 100)
- Response format: `{ count, next, previous, results }`

## Pagination DTO

```typescript
export class PaginationDto {
  @IsOptional()
  @Type(() => Number)
  @Min(1)
  page?: number = 1;

  @IsOptional()
  @Type(() => Number)
  @Min(1)
  @Max(100)
  pageSize?: number = 20;
}
```

## Response Format

```typescript
{
  count: 150,
  next: "https://api.hochu.com/api/requests?page=2",
  previous: null,
  results: [...]
}
```

## Filtering

- Filter through query parameters in DTO
- Support multiple filters simultaneously
- Use TypeORM query builder for complex filters

## Sorting

Sorting through `sort` query parameter:
- `sort=createdAt` - Sort by creation date (ASC)
- `sort=-createdAt` - Sort by creation date (DESC)
- `sort=price` - Sort by price (ASC)
- `sort=-price` - Sort by price (DESC)
- `sort=rating` - Sort by rating (ASC)
- `sort=-rating` - Sort by rating (DESC)

## Search

- Full-text search on `title` and `description` fields
- Use FULLTEXT index in MySQL/MariaDB
- Or use Elasticsearch for complex cases

## Implementation

```typescript
async findAll(dto: GetRequestsDto) {
  const { page = 1, pageSize = 20, ...filters } = dto;
  const skip = (page - 1) * pageSize;

  const query = this.repository.createQueryBuilder('request');
  
  // Apply filters
  if (filters.category) {
    query.andWhere('request.category = :category', { category: filters.category });
  }
  
  // Apply sorting
  if (filters.sort) {
    const order = filters.sort.startsWith('-') ? 'DESC' : 'ASC';
    const field = filters.sort.replace('-', '');
    query.orderBy(`request.${field}`, order);
  }
  
  const [results, count] = await query
    .skip(skip)
    .take(pageSize)
    .getManyAndCount();
  
  return {
    count,
    next: page * pageSize < count ? `?page=${page + 1}` : null,
    previous: page > 1 ? `?page=${page - 1}` : null,
    results,
  };
}
```
